Aon plc Key Developments

Aon plc Declares Quarterly Cash Dividend, Payable on August 15, 2017
Jul 14 17
Aon plc announced that the board of directors has declared a quarterly cash dividend of $0.36 per share on outstanding Class A Ordinary Shares. The dividend is payable August 15, 2017 to shareholders of record on August 1, 2017.


Aon plc - Shareholder/Analyst Call
May 25 17
Annual General Meeting of Shareholders


Aon Benfield Develops IFRS 17 Solution for Kyobo Life
May 15 17
Aon Benfield announced the launch of its PathWise® Solutions Group IFRS 17business solutions package - an integrated enterprise High Performance Computing (HPC) business platform for this important emerging financial reporting framework. The platform has been adopted for IFRS 17 purposes by Kyobo Life Insurance Co Ltd. PathWise allows businesses to model assets, liabilities, and scenario generators at the same time, thereby providing a complete solution for the managing and reporting of complex financial and biometric risks. The HPC software runs on Graphics Processing Units (GPUs), giving it a speed advantage over other legacy systems which run on Central Processing Units (CPUs), for all the new calculations required under the IFRS 17 standard. In addition, unlike many legacy systems all logic and calculations are completely transparent, making PathWise a highly flexible platform which comes with exhaustive audit trails and controls, and which is 'big data' ready out of the box, to help manage all the new assumptions and data required under IFRS 17. PathWise is replacing Kyobo's existing reserve valuation tool with an end-to-end fully automated system that handles inforce conversion, assumption transformation, scenario generation, stochastic-on stochastic calculations and financial report generation.


